Unofficial Translation by Insurance Regulator of Cambodia (IRC)

*   A copy and certified by the notary of approval letter of the competent authority of the country of origin to conduct insurance business in the Kingdom of Cambodia;
*   A copy with the company seal of documents about the background and structure of the parent company or the principal;
*   A copy with the company seal of audited financial statements of the parent company or the principal for the last 5 (five) years;
*   the document about rating of the parent company or the principal evaluated by the international rating agency (if any);
*   A copy of final inspection report of the regulator of the country of origin (if any).

After reviewing and evaluating the above required documents, the **IRC** has the right to issue a principle approval or reject the application within 60 (sixty) days from the date of receipt of sufficient documents. The **IRC** provide this principle approval to the applicant for business registration with the Ministry of Commerce and continue with other procedures as necessary.

**Article 7 ..**

After obtaining the principle approval for conducting general insurance business or life insurance business or a foreign insurance company business branch and have registered business in accordance with the law of Kingdom of Cambodia, the insurance company shall apply for general insurance company business license or life insurance company business license or foreign insurance company business branch by attaching the required documents as below:
- the application for general insurance company business license or life insurance company business license or foreign insurance company business branch signed by the chairman of the board of directors or the authorized director from the board;
- the company's declaration form completed and signed by the chairman of the board of directors or the authorized director from the board in the form prescribed by the Director General of the Insurance Regulator of Cambodia;
- A copy with the company seal of principle approval to conduct general insurance business or life insurance business or foreign insurance company business branch;
- the receipt of administrative fee;
- the receipt of license fee;
- A copy with the company seal of company's memorandum of association and business registration certificate of a company in the form of a Public Limited Company;
- the documents on the structure and composition of the management team with the company seal;
- the document on Underwriting Policy approved by board of directors with the company seal;
- the document on Claim Policy approved by board of directors with the company seal;
- the document on Risk Management Policy approved by board of directors with the company seal;
- the document on Corporate Governance Policy approved by board of directors with the company seal;
- the document on Complaint and Dispute Settlement Policy approved by board of directors with the company seal;
- the document on Accounting and Finance Policy approved by board of directors with the company seal;
- the document on Anti-money Laundering and Combating the Financing of Terrorism and Combating the Financing of Proliferation of Weapons of Mass Destruction Policy approved by board of directors with the company seal;

